jackr@dblues.wpd.sgi.com (John Jack Repenning) writes:

> If you read a public newsgroup, it turns out what you see is posts to
> public newsgroups; this phenomenon has mystified sages through the
> ages, but it says nothing at all about what other uses there might be,
> and which are the "major purposes of public key crypto."  Indeed, I'd
> just as soon people didn't routinely sign their postings.
> 

I think to a large degree that PGP signatures have become a form
of social protest. It has become the moral equivalent in cyberspace of
wearing an American flag lapel pin to the Rotary Club luncheon.


